# OrcheStack code owners.
#
# Every line is a glob followed by one or more @usernames who own the
# matched paths. When branch protection requires CODEOWNERS approval, a
# PR cannot merge until at least one named owner has approved it.
#
# This file is parsed top-to-bottom; later rules override earlier ones.

# ── Default ownership ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Every change requires maintainer review.
*                                       @tripleaceme

# ── Maintainer-only areas (already-default, listed for documentation) ─
# These paths are listed explicitly so contributors searching CODEOWNERS
# for "what's off-limits" find an authoritative answer. The CONTRIBUTING
# guide names the same paths.

# Brand and visual identity — every change requires design review.
/assets/                                @tripleaceme

# Release machinery — single maintainer owns release cadence + secrets.
/.github/workflows/release.yml          @tripleaceme
/Makefile                               @tripleaceme
/scripts/build-bundle.sh                @tripleaceme

# Licence and project-level governance.
/LICENSE                                @tripleaceme
/SECURITY.md                            @tripleaceme
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md                     @tripleaceme
/CODEOWNERS                             @tripleaceme
/.github/CODEOWNERS                     @tripleaceme
